node.text:
We place so much of our happiness into the hands of others.

So much of our worth, whether that’s feeling sexy or feeling adequate enough to be successful.

It’s not taught to us that we truly have the power to fulfill all our own needs. That statement itself gives me chills, because YOU can place that happiness within yourself.

You have the power to be your bestfriend, hype women, lover, and fufill the void that others aren’t filling.

So choose yourself, you fulfill your own needs.

node.title: One Affirmation That Can Change Your Life

node.text:
Want a healthy brownie that tastes EXACTLY like a real one?

I gotchu, stay hydrated b*tches. I make this every single night all cozy in my pjs-my favorite recipe I’ve posted yet!

Recipe:
1 tbsp dairy free butter
1/4 cup flour
1-1 1/2 tbsp coconut sugar
2 tbsp cocoa powder
1 scoop collagen protein
1 tsp vanilla
1 tbsp peanut butter
Splash of baking soda
1/4 cup water

Microwave for 1-2 minutes and enjoy an ooey gooey brownie!

#thedailysculpt #sculptyou

node.text:
Move over Mickey D’s we got some new nuggets in the house

I love making my own chicken nuggets at home (also can make in the air fryer) for a little snack with some ketchup, also helps beat fast food cravings!

All you need:
coconut or almond flour, egg whites, and panko. I seasoned mine with salt, paprika, and garlic!

Dip cut up chicken in the flour, egg whites, then panko. Put into the air fryer or oven at 400 for 10 minutes!

If you’re vegan you can use tofu and sub coconut oil for the egg whites!

Hope you all enjoy❤️🙏🏼

node.text:
A mood after getting back to the gym after not lifting anything heavy for months or hearing loud sexual grunting 24/7

I am now ovulating and have pulled not just one but multiple of my hips

This is a complete comedic joke for anyone watching lmao, and please be careful getting back into the gym. Lose the ego and focus on form and not pushing extreme weight! Also take all the precautions necessary (without spraying someone entirely with Lysol) to protect yourself and others from the Coronavirus

Pls enjoy

node.text:
IT IS HERE

my favorite recipe of all time: healthy vegan donuts that you’ll want to have for dessert every night

Recipe:

INGREDIENTS
1 cup of flour (I used einkorn flour but you can also use whole wheat, pastry flour, or a gluten free 1–1 substitute)
1/2 teaspoon of baking soda
teaspoon of baking powder
pinch of salt
1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon
1/4 cup of maple syrup
1/2 cup of almond milk
3 tablespoons of nut butter
1 teaspoon of vanilla extract
1 medium banana, mashed

Mix all together and bake for 10 minutes at 350.

You can also put them into balls and make them in the air fryer or oven if you don’t have a donut pan!

#thedailysculpt #sculptyou

node.text:
Another Tuesday healthy recipe video coming @ you that is worth waiting until the end

Today we have grain free nachos with dairy free cheese!! When looking for potato chips or any plain chip, I like to go by the three or four ingredient rule. potato/grain, non inflammatory oil (avocado, coconut, etc), and sea salt

Will continue to bring you guys recipes every Tuesday, but will be bringing a twist to them!

My eyes have been more than opened to the racial injustices in our food and healthcare system, I plan on shining light on those and bringing to you all recipes that can be made with adorable ingredients you can find anywhere. Hope you all have a blessed day!! #thedailysculpt #sculptyou

node.text:
This is an absolute troll on my morning routine, please enjoy

But it rings true!! So important to have structure in the morning for myself. To set myself up with a focus for the day and come into the day with a clear mind/try to release any tension in my body

Every morning consists of my skincare routine, mediation (@thesculptyou or the calm app), and journaling.

Also I never chuck my journal off the balcony it was a one time stunt do not try that at home lmao

Figure out what works for you and start your day like a boss

#thedailysculpt #sculptyou

node.text:
One of my favorite recipes I’ve ever made, is finally here

High protein dairy free Mac and cheese coming at you

All you need is:
1/2 block or 1 small block of silken tofu
1/4 cup coconut milk
2 tsp (or more depending on your taste) of garlic salt
Dairy free cheese + butter I personally use @miyokoscreamery 
Elbow pasta

Blend tofu, milk, and garlic salt together to create a sauce. Mix with buttered elbow pasta, and top with cheese!

Hope you enjoy this recipe and let me know what you think if you try it out!

#thedailysculpt #sculptyou

node.text:
I absolutely love this question-and the answer is simple but very complex

Choose yourself.

I know what you’re thinking-wtf does that mean.

It means, look internally and see what you’re seeking from others.

It’s time to give that to yourself. When you are whole within yourself, you don’t need to seek outside validation because you provide it.

A partner adds to your life and elevates you-you don’t deserve to wait to be chosen. Step in and choose yourself.

#thedailysculpt #scultpyou

node.text:
Tonight I’m bringing you 3 of my favorite super easy healthy desserts to curb that sweet tooth. All of these take less than 5 minutes!

Air fried dates: fill up a date with almond butter and place in air fryer for 3 minutes. Can also use a microwave! Top with chocolate and enjoy!

Fried Bananas: sauté bananas in a pan with coconut oil, cinnamon, honey, and Himalayan salt until crispy!

And the easiest one- put some chocolate into a raspberry and call it a night!

Hope you all enjoyed!

#thedailysculpt #sculptyou

node.text:
Bringing a new segment called chit chat with Kat!! I wanted to answer questions on all things lifestyle/love/relationships as mental and physical health doesn’t stop with the gym and nutrition, your mindset is everything

Trust me, I know the “mindset is everything” slogan can cause you to roll your eyes, because there’s so much pain/trauma behind every thought you may have.

But, these simple shifts build up. The simple realization to recognizing this life only has ONE of you can shift to then a daily dedication of you appreciating the deepest parts of your soul that nobody else has

Recognize your unique internal beauty, and know that reflects outwards. There are always going to be beautiful people on this earth, but that doesn’t take away anything from you-you are worthy

#thedailysculpt #sculptyou

node.title: “I don’t feel physically good enough for my man”

node.text:
Raw bathroom talk goin up on a Tuesday

Let’s talk self worth: how do you raise it?

Take a look at what you WANT to feel and WHO you want to be-you hold the power in who you want to create.

There’s been dark moments of my past, but I refuse to let it define my future as I live everyday creating someone I’m proud of. That’s where you build your self worth.

You are NOT worth feeling less than, take the reigns in your life. Don’t look back and settle for being treated less than you deserve, step into your power!

This is easier said than done, and a daily process. But I promise you, incredibly worth the work.

My May challenge closes tonight! So excited for this month with you all!

#thdailysculpt #sculptyou

node.text:
Guess we have more work to do😭😂 got my heart and my glutes pumpin, the motivation a gym crush provides is unmatched

A gym crush is like having your very own free personal trainer. They push you, motivate you to get there at a certain time, and sometimes get you to do recovery work just to stay there a little longer in case you both catch eyes.

I’m telling ya, Kris Jenner works hard but a gym crush works harder. To be able to get me off my ass is a magical feat. To get me to do cardio so you can maybe see these cheeks clappin for you is the work of an angel. S/o to my forever gym crush @mckenna_dylan

node.text:
Call me so I can make it juicy for ya🍌⬇️

I remember when I first started my fitness journey I would Google “how to grow my legs + glutes”, I would DM people on Instagram that inspired me, and I was simply standing there like 👁👄👁 who tf has the secret crabby patty formula

It’s not as crazy as the internet makes you believe.

I simply had to stop: following random workouts, not doing any compound movements and just using random machines, eating minimal calories, excessive amounts of cardio on the stair master, and comparing myself to others- all it did was bring me down and not enjoy training or push myself.

I had to: focus on the basics (not the crazy movements you see), focus on form + progressive overload, feed my body good, and GIVE IT CONSISTENCY AND TIME.

If you have any questions ask me below!❤️

node.text:
Block it OUT‼️ reminder that every single person has walked into the weight room not knowing what they are doing.

It’s okay if you
🤍feel like your form is wrong
🤍don’t know how to use machines
🤍feel as if others are going to judge you, or feel fear being the only woman in the free weight section

You are not alone. I have used every single machine wrong. It took me a year of staring at the weights from the treadmill to even walk over there. I have fallen on my ass multiple times. I have split my leggings, and I have gotten my period through my leggings more times than I can count lmao.

The point is-the gym is meant to be a place where you can push through your negative self talk, so you can develop a stronger self physically and mentally. The journey is the best part. If anyone judges you for it, they are projecting a deeper insecurity onto you and they can kiss this a$$. You are not meant to live a life out of fear of others opinions.

And that also applies to your fitness journey, and I know that’s something I damn well needed to hear at the beginning as I watched from afar. You CAN do this. Have fun with it, and block it tf out

node.text:
When I think about one of my best (& sexiest) first dates, I think about the first date I ever took myself on.

I was in college. I can’t even explain to you the fear I had of being alone. I had fear of just sitting with myself with my own thoughts, I would always try to surround myself with my roommates or cling on to any romantic interest I could regardless of how shitty it made me feel. This created a distant feeling within myself-did I even know who I am? What made me happy?

This fear created a person that was waiting to experience things and truly live life. I was waiting for a healthy relationship or someone to come and distract me from sh*t falling apart in my life to do things I wanted to do. I would say “wouldn’t that be nice to do that with someone.”

Why tf couldn’t I do it myself?

I got myself dressed up, took a journal, and went to the farmers market. I explored-talking to vendors about what lights them up, trying local health foods, and asking myself questions along the way like I would a first date. My soul was fired up-this is sh*t I love. Then, I went home..and let me just tell you, I didn’t just connect with myself emotionally but we had a damn good time in the bubble bath at my apartment.

Now years later I have had so many self dates that I’ll never forget, but the farmers market will forever be one of the places that makes me happiest. As there’s so many pieces of it that I connect to, and show me that there’s so many things in life that light me up without relying on another soul but my own. I sourced that for myself. And it’s a damn beautiful thing, and I encourage you all little by little to find your own light sources

node.text:
This is the vibe we be on‼️ I am at the gym to focus on me and myself only, but if you choose to make me feel uncomfortable I will stare you down real mfing QUICK

I refuse to allow someone make me feel uncomfortable in my safe space. This doesn’t just go for eyes on me, but I’ve had people make fun of me in the gym while filming/men come up to me and comment on my form or physique/women laugh with their friends at me during the beginning of my weight training journey.

I will not hold myself back due to the actions of others, as it’s a reflection of them-not myself.

So here’s to staring back at creeps, standing up for ourselves (please report if needed-I’ve done many times!), and not allowing others to hold real estate in our minds.

node.text:
If you’re tryna blow up those two blueberries on your backside like Willy Wonkas chocolate factory, I gotchu

This was the first workout of my July challenge, it’s been two days and I’m still unwell

Some cues for you for legs:
🤍when you squat, pretend you are pulling the floor apart with your feet (it automatically shifts tension to your glutes, forces you to push knees out)
🤍utilize eccentrics in your training. Eccentrics meaning the portion of the exercise where the muscle is lengthening. @train_centric is a great app that allows you to time your eccentrics/concentrics..because a 3 second eccentric when your booty is burning feels like FOREVER
🤍if you aren’t feeling maximum glute tension or able to maintain proper form and full ROM, your bench may be too high-try putting plates under your feet.
🤍can sub hip abduction for the last movement, it was taken so I did a glute med kickbacks-in my opinion feel more glute engagement with those!

Let me know if you try this out and what you think!

node.text:
if you’re tryna swallow up someone’s face with those booty cheeks, you’re in the right place⬇️

What are the main contributors to glute growth?
🤍nutrition-are you achieving an adequate amount of protein/complex carbs/healthy fats
🤍training with intention-are you just going through the movements or are you optimizing your form for maximal glute engagement, mind-muscle connection, and control
🤍compound movements/structure/consistency- are you changing things up every single time you go to the gym, or are you on a structured plan utilizing compound lifts and progressive overload? Your glutes are your largest muscle-they need to receive consistent stress to react/build
🤍bioindividuality- we are all build differently. So focus and discover what movements (and variants of the movement) you truly feel the best glute engagement. Don’t compare, focus on your journey

Here’s a workout that has some of my fav glute movements (others not included that are staples for me: squats, box squats, split squats, leg press, lunge variants, single leg hip thrusts, back extensions)

Hope you enjoy this one and if you have any questions let me know!⬇️

Its JULY FIERI. Welcome to Triple D nation-Donuts, Deadlifts, and Dumptrucks. @thesculptyou July challenge is now LIVE! Link in bio

This month in flavortown we are bringin the HEAT.

I spent so many years of my life fearing food. I was horrified of high fat, carbs, and numbers-not understanding that the female body thrives on healthy fats and carbohydrates. Not understanding that MY BODY IS A MIRACLE ON A DAMN FLOATING ROCK! And I am not here to live off fear of numbers. And I can eat the mfing donut without hating myself for it.

This month in The Sculpt You our goal is to build a more healthy relationship with food, bring in more foods that nourish us, and honor our cravings without judgement. Our Registered Dietitian will be focusing on carbohydrate and fat education-dispelling myths and empowering you with your food choices. We also just launched our incredible intuitive eating meal plan section (vegan, hormone health, IBS friendly) to help you with this journey!

So this month thigh fieri is gonna be BUILDING THIS CAKE‼️‼️ and we are giving ourselves the grace to eat it too while nourishing our bodies physically, spiritually, emotionally, and through food!

Challenge is included in my $9 program always, so excited for this next month!

These simple shifts in your form will change the 🍑 GAME‼️

Single leg RDLs are not only incredible for sculpting/building your hammies and glutes, but they are also an amazing core movement

If you are having trouble balancing, place your leg back on a bench or keep foot placed on the ground slightly behind the leg that is forward

Sit back into your glute, keeping the dumbbell against your leg, and pulling up with your glute right below your knee to maintain that glute/hamstring tension and not allow your lower back to take over

Hope this helped with this movement!❤️ if you have any questions comment below!

Be the one to gas yourself tf up.

I will be the first one to admit that the question “do you think I look pretty/good/hot/sexy” has left my mouth so many times throughout my romantic and non-romantic relationships.

Do I look good enough in this picture? In the bedroom? When Im thicck or do you like me leaner? Do you like me with blonde or dark hair?

Their approval was a drug. Think about it this way...suddenly someone saying I’m beautiful made me “enough.” Not my soul, my personality, my passion, my drive, my vulnerability..but if someone thought I looked good enough in a picture to post it.

I’d stalk women that men I was talking to have dated, comparing every single part of myself to them. I’d stalk pictures on Instagram wishing I could look differently.

But heres your huge reminder: if you fuel your self worth on the opinions of others, you are gonna run out of gas.

How can your worth be decided by anyone outside of you-when you are the one who truly sees EVERYTHING you are.

What do YOU think about that picture? About your hair/how you physically feel in your body? Start striving to fill your needs, refill your gas tank, and reminding yourself that you deserve to be loved for how you were created. So squats low, standards high mfers

node.text:
If you were to look back on your favorite memories, do they have anything to do with your body?

With how you looked that day? With what you weighed that day? Do you remember the size of the clothes you wore?

My parents and I laughed over old stories and memories this weekend, and as I looked back on those memories the pure joy of that moment was all I could remember.

But as I hugged my dad goodbye, tears rolled down my face. For years of my life, I wasn’t present with my family and friends. The entirety of our time together I would be absorbed by thoughts of how I looked, how uncomfortable I felt in my body, fear of food, or distracting myself with my phone.

This weekend I soaked in and reminded myself some of my favorite things about life: warm hugs, coffee in the morning, a warm fresh donut, drinking wine and laughing with my mom. Not one of the little things that I will cherish so much when my loved ones are gone, have to do with my physical.

So I will continue to build a life where I see the universe wants me to experience life exactly as I am, it’s up to me to see the beauty in that and all the little things.

What is one of your favorite memories? Does it have anything to do with how you looked?

HEALTHY COOKIE DOUGH BLIZZARD🍪 (gluten and dairy free)

This is one of the yummiest & easiest recipes of all time, you can also add protein powder to the cookie dough or ice cream if you’d like!

(I personally mix the dough with collagen protein and just eat that on its own, so good!)

For the dough:
1/4 cup cashew butter
1/2 cup almond flour
1 tsp vanilla
1 tbsp pure maple syrup
Pinch of salt
Chocolate chips (I use HU or enjoy life)

For the ice cream:
1 ripe frozen bananas
1/4 cup almond milk
1 tsp vanilla
1 tsp monk fruit
Chocolate bar (I use HU or enjoy life)

Let me know what you think!❤️
